<subSubSection id="6FF9CC0A9FE56E0EFBC8965EDF94A3DF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="E02C39F0F54DD335BDD8B3EDB3D8DBE9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="33F939983C844319A75CAC0B12DBF6A0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Twining subshrub to 1.5 m; stems glabrous, woody when old, strongly warted. Leaves petiolate, dimorphic, 2.5-4 
<normalizedToken id="AB89C79CFC9398A768B0998AFD4671D7" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 cm, ovate cordate or, more commonly deeply 3-5-lobed with apical lobe elliptic, much larger than the laterals, apex obtuse, lobes contracted at base, both surfaces glabrous; petioles 1-2.2 cm. Inflorescence of axillary pedunculate cymes; peduncles 0.5-2.5 cm, glabrous, slightly warted; bracteoles 1.5-2 mm, ovate, obtuse, caducous; secondary peduncles 5-7 mm; pedicels relatively slender, 7-10 mm; sepals subequal, 5-7 mm long, oblong-elliptic, obtuse, glabrous, the inner ones with a rounded scarious apex; corolla 3-4.5 cm long, glabrous, hypocrateriform, the tube 2.5-3.3 cm, pale, limb 0.7-0.9 cm in diam., lobed, lobes deep red, 4-6 mm long, ovate, often reflexed; stamens exserted. Capsules ovoid, glabrous, c. 10 mm long; seeds 5 
<normalizedToken id="1707EC8575058F1198B6717DC58A0A97" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5 mm, pilose with long marginal hairs to 8 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
